  "doc_id": "26968",
  "text": "The study was conducted in Suanphung District of Thailand in a population that has been involved in malaria epidemiological studies since 1995. The characteristics of this population have been previously described [CITATION_1] , with people identifying themselves as Karen (85%), Thai (14%), and the remaining Mon and Burmese (1%). Family structures, G6PD phenotype, and G6PD genotype, along with nearby markers on the X chromosome, were previously ascertained in a study examining selection of G6PD deficiency on P. vivax infection among this population [CITATION_2] . ",
